div.p:
It was agreed:
—to issue a NSSM calling for a study of the general question of naval arms control;The NSSM was drafted only. See Document 63.
—that we are not prepared to accept any deployment limitations on SSBNs in the Indian Ocean;
—to prepare a more specific paper on the question of naval deployment limitations for presenation to the President, and that nothing would be discussed with any government prior to a Presidential decision;
—State will prepare talking points for the President’s meeting with Prime Minister Bandaranaike and obtain agency views on them;Briefing material, including the Talking Points, are in the National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials, NSC Files, Box 592, Country Files, Middle East, Ceylon, Vol. I.
—our instructions to our UN Delegation on the Ceylonese proposal will be based on the President’s conversation with Mrs. Bandaranaike.
